OL,3,GNorth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FA damp
OL,6,Fevening for some with occasional
OL,7,Fshowery rain and drizzle. This tending
OL,8,Fto become mostly confined to higher
OL,9,Fground for a time overnight, but
OL,10,Fperhaps turning more generally wet
OL,11,Fagain later. Mild and often breezy,
OL,12,Fwindy over the hills.
OL,13,
OL,14,CFriday:FCloudy for many first thing
OL,15,Fwith further showery rain. Becoming
OL,16,Flargely dry by the afternoon with
OL,17,Fsunny spells developing. Feeling much
OL,18,Fwarmer than on Thursday but remaining
OL,19,Frather blustery.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
